Executive Profile
Gordon D. Harnett  Independent Director, Acuity Brands, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships74$205,000
Background

		Mr. Gordon D. Harnett served as the Chief Executive Officer of Materion Corporation (formerly, Brush Engineered Materials Inc., and Brush Wellman Inc) from January 1991 to May 2006 and President from May 2002 to May 2006. Mr. Harnett served as a Senior Vice President of The B.F. Goodrich Co. from 1987 to 1991 and as President of Tremco Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of The B.F. Goodrich Co., from 1982 to 1985 and Chief Executive Officer from 1985 to 1987. He worked ... for McKinsey & Co., including a two-year assignment in Tokyo from 1969 to 1976. He served as Non-Executive Chairman at EnPro Industries, Inc. from 2010 to April 26, 2017. He serves as the Chairman of Materion Brush Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Cleveland Development Advisors Inc. and the Greater Cleveland International Trade Alliance. He served as the Chairman of Materion Corporation from January 1991 to May 2006. He has been an Independent Director of Acuity Brands, Inc. since January 2009. He served as an Independent Director at Enpro Industries Inc from May 21, 2002 to April 26, 2017. He served as a Director of PolyOne Corporation since 1997 and served as its Lead Director since July 18, 2007 until May 14, 2015. Mr. Harnett served as Director of Materion Corporation from January 1991 to June 2, 2006. He served as Lead outside Director of The Lubrizol Corporation and served as its Director from 1995 to September 16, 2011. He served as a Director of Essef Corp. since July 1987. Mr. Harnett served as a Director of M.A. Hanna Company since 1997. He served as a Director of National City Bank. He serves as a Trustee of University Hospitals of Cleveland, Cleveland Tomorrow and Greater Cleveland Growth Association. He served as a Trustee of Manufacturers Alliance for Productivity and Innovation, Inc. Mr. Harnett graduated from Miami University in 1964 with a B.S. Degree in Business Administration. He received an M.B.A. from Harvard University in 1969.Read Full Background




